					<h2 class="heading--2">Accelerating vulnerability management processes</h2>
					<p class="paragraph--2">
						Glenn Pegden, Security Vulnerability Manager at Sky Betting & Gaming, says: <b>“<em>In recent years, the velocity of our work has dramatically increased. Cyber-attackers are more nimble and more sophisticated, which means it's no longer acceptable to set service-level agreements [SLAs] of 90, 60 or even 30 days for many vulnerability management tasks. However, it's all but impossible to accelerate these processes while relying on large, complicated spreadsheets to keep track of open vulnerabilities.</em>”</b>
